The paper discusses compressed sensing with variable density sampling, which is a common topic in the information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP) sub-categories. The paper also deals with the sparsity structure of the underlying signal, which is relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper presents theoretical guarantees for tight frames, which is a topic in the computational complexity (cs.CC) sub-category.
